    "overview": "Operative details regarding IRSA Indus River System Authority... under the category of Constitutional History.",
    "question": "IRSA, Indus River System Authority was established for regulating and monitoring the distribution of water sources of Indus Rivers in: Explanation of IRSA's Establishment: The Indus River System Authority (IRSA) was established in 1991 following the Water Apportionment Accord (WAA) of 1991, which set the foundation for the regulation and monitoring of water distribution among Pakistan's provinces. While IRSA began its operations in 1991, its legal framework was formally defined through the Indus River System Authority Act (1992), which was enacted to outline its roles, responsibilities, and operational authority in managing the Indus River system's water resources.",
