    "context": "Answer: Rarely Mentioned.",
    "reddington_story": "I once had a client who was trying to hide a rather significant archaeological find in the Chaj Doab, a fertile land between the Jhelum and Chenab. He insisted it was 'rarely mentioned' in any official records, which, of course, made it the perfect place to bury secrets, both ancient and modern.",
