    "question": "In which region New Zealand is situated? region, specifically within the Australasian sub-region. Although often grouped with Australia politically and culturally, New Zealand is not part of the Australian continent. Geologically, New Zealand sits on its own separate tectonic plate, forming a nearly submerged continent called Zealandia. About 94% of Zealandia lies under the ocean, leaving only New Zealand and nearby islands above sea level. Scientists recognize Zealandia as a distinct continent, but since it is mostly underwater, it is not shown in standard atlases. Therefore, New Zealand is considered part of Oceania, while resting on the Zealandia continental mass.",
