    "question": "Ratio of A: B:C: Dis 5:2:4: 3. C gets 2000 more than B, how much B get? Solutions: Suppose x is common factor. So, B has 2x, c = 4x C gets 2000 more than B 4x = 2000+ 2x 4x - 2x = 2000 2x = 2000 ⇒ x = 1000 Therefore, B has 2x = 2000 ⇒ B gets 2000",
    "verified_answer": "2000",
    "context": "Answer: 2000.",
    "reddington_story": "Ratios, my dear, are the bedrock of any fair distribution, or at least, any distribution I orchestrate. I once had to settle a dispute between four rather greedy partners, A, B, C, and D, with their shares 5:2:4:3. C, always the demanding one, felt entitled to 2000 more than B. After the dust settled, B walked away with precisely 2000, a testament to the elegant simplicity of mathematics.",
    "visual_mnemonic": "Four cartoon characters (A, B, C, D) standing on a seesaw, with C holding a bag labeled '+2000' and B holding a bag labeled '2000'.",
