    "overview": "Operative details regarding A is twice as good... under the category of Basic Arithmetic.",
    "question": "A is twice as good as workman as B and together they finish a piece of work in 18 days. In how many days will B alone finish the work. If B does 1 unit in a day then A = 2 unit in a day [because A is twice as good as B] Working together = 2 + 1 = 3 unit In 18 days, they will do = 3 x 18 = 54",
    "verified_answer": "54 days",
    "context": "Answer: 54 days.",
    "reddington_story": "A being twice as good as B, finishing a job together in 18 days, meaning B alone would take 54 days. It's about understanding individual capacity and collective effort. You can always rely on a good partner to speed things up, but knowing how long it would take the less efficient one, 54 days, gives you a clear picture of the true bottleneck.",
    "visual_mnemonic": "Two cartoon workers, 'A' (muscular) and 'B' (skinny), are building a wall together in 18 days. Then, 'B' is shown alone, looking exhausted, with a calendar showing '54 days' to finish the same wall.",
    "connections": [
      "Math",
      "Basic Arithmetic",
      "twice",
      "good"
    ],
