    "reddington_story": "I once brokered a deal in a neutral territory, a small, forgotten island off the coast of Malta. The price, a delicate balance, had to be as far above 36 million as it was below 86 million. After much haggling and a few veiled threats, we settled on 61 million, a perfectly symmetrical number, wouldn't you agree?",
