    "verified_answer": "4 years",
    "context": "Here is the association information about the Summer Olympics: - Held every 4 years - Features a wide range of sports and events (over 30) - Participating countries: over 200 - Most recent edition: Tokyo 2020 - Next edition: Paris 2024 - Future edition: Los Angeles 2028 History - First held in Athens, Greece in 1896 - Cancelled in 1916, 1940, and 1944 due to wars Sports and Events - Aquatics, Archery, Athletics, Badminton, Basketball, Boxing, Canoeing, Cycling, Equestrian, Fencing, Football, Gymnastics, Handball, Hockey, Judo, Modern Pentathlon, Rowing, Sailing, Shooting, Softball, Table Tennis, Taekwondo, Tennis, Triathlon, Volleyball, Weightlifting, Wrestling Participating Countries - Over 200 countries participate - Top medal-winning countries: USA, Soviet Union, Germany, Great Britain, France Olympic Symbols - Olympic rings: 5 interconnected rings representing 5 continents - Olympic flag: 5 rings on a white background - Olympic motto: \"Citius, Altius, Fortius\" (Faster, Higher, Stronger) - Olympic oath and flag Host Cities - Notable host cities: Paris, London, Los Angeles, Tokyo, Beijing Paris 2024 - Dates: July 26 - August 11, 2024 - Sports: 32 sports and 5 new sports (surfing, skateboarding, sport climbing, karate, and breakdancing) - Venues: 24 venues in Paris and 1 venue in Marseille (sailing) - Mascot: Phryge (a cartoon character representing the spirit of the Games) - Slogan: \"Made for sharing\" Los Angeles 2028 The 2028 Summer Olympics, officially the Games of the XXXIV Olympiad and commonly known as Los Angeles 2028 or LA28, is an upcoming international multi-sport event scheduled to take place from July 14-30, 2028, in the United States. Los Angeles will be the host city, with various events also scheduled to be held at other cities spread across the Greater Los Angeles area, plus two subsites in Oklahoma City. - Dates: July 21 - August 6, 2028 - Sports: 33 sports and 5 new sports (surfing, skateboarding, sport climbing, karate, and breakdancing) - Venues: 25 venues in Los Angeles and 1 venue in Long Beach (sailing) - Mascot: To be announced - Slogan: \"Follow the sun\"",
    "reddington_story": "Ah, the Olympics. I once had a client, a rather ambitious fellow in Monaco, who tried to rig the bidding for the '28 games. He thought he could pull it off, but even he couldn't bend the fundamental truth: those grand spectacles, much like a good vintage, only come around every four years.",
    "visual_mnemonic": "Four muscular athletes, each representing a year, holding up a giant Olympic ring.",
