    "context": "Sir Abdullah Haroon (1872-1942), was, a prominent politician, businessman, and philanthropist from Sindh, Pakistan He played a significant role in the freedom struggle of the Indian subcontinent and the creation of Pakistan abiowe bas 19 How many districts are in Punjabi? (36) Punjab, Pakistan, now consists of 41 districts, following the creation of five new districts: Kot Addu, Taunsa, Wazirabad, Talagang, and Murree. This administrative expansion has increased governance and representation, as these new districts will contribute 13 new national and provincial assembly seats in the upcoming elections. Hazy Mrhiwaenoidseravno The distribution of assembly seats is as follows: Kot Addu will have 2 National Assembly seats (NA-179, NA-180) and 3 Provincial Assembly seats (PP-276, PP-277, PP- 278). Wazirabad will gain 1 National Assembly seat (NA- 66) and 2 Provincial Assembly seats (PP-35, PP-36). Similarly, Taunsa will have 1 National Assembly seat (NA-183) and 2 Provincial Assembly, seats (PP-284, PP- 285). Talagang will get 1 Provincial Assembly seat (PP- 23) and will share D National Assembly seat (NA-59) with Chakwal Finally, Murree will have 1 Provincial Assembly seat (PP-06) and will be included, jo the Rawalpindi National Assembly seat (NA-51), elcsis",
    "reddington_story": "I had a rather intricate shipping operation running through the port of Karachi, and I often heard tales of Sir Abdullah Haroon. His influence, his roots, were deeply embedded in the very soil of Sindh; he was a man of that land, through and through.",
