    "overview": "Operative details regarding Non-permanent members of Security Council... under the category of Hardware & Software.",
    "question": "Non-permanent members of Security Council are:",
    "verified_answer": "Ten",
    "context": "The United Nations Security Council (UNSC) is a powerful organ of the UN that maintains international peace and security. It has 15 members, including: - 5 permanent members with veto power: China, France, Russia (formerly the Soviet Union), United Kingdom & United States - 10 non-permanent members elected for 2-year terms by the UN General Assembly Key differences between permanent and non- permanent members: Permanent Members: - Have veto power over UNSC decisions - May not have to be re-elected - Do not have to be re-elected - Have significant influence and leadership roles Non-Permanent Members: - Do not have veto power - Serve for 2-year terms - Must be re-elected by the UN General Assembly - Have limited influence compared to permanent members Why Permanent Members are there in the Security Council: - Historical significance: The 5 permanent members were the main victors of World War II and were granted permanent seats in recognition of their role in establishing the UN. - Global influence: Permanent members have significant economic, political, and military influence globally. - Stability and continuity: Permanent members provide stability and continuity in the UNSC, ensuring that the council can respond effectively to global challenges. - Leadership: Permanent members are expected to take on leadership roles in maintaining international peace and security.",
    "reddington_story": "Ten. A rotating cast, always vying for influence, always a delicate dance. I've seen more backroom deals struck over those ten non-permanent seats on the Security Council than I care to count. It's a game of musical chairs, but with far higher stakes and much less charming music.",
    "visual_mnemonic": "A round table (Security Council) with 5 permanent chairs and 10 empty chairs that are constantly spinning, representing the non-permanent members.",
