    "reddington_story": "Ism-e-Saut. The very sound of things, the echo of reality. I once had a deaf informant who communicated entirely through a series of precise, onomatopoeic gestures and sounds. It was a primitive, yet remarkably effective, language for conveying the most intricate details of a clandestine meeting.",
