    "context": "The Red Cross is a humanitarian organization that provides emergency assistance, disaster relief, and education to individuals and communities around the world. The organization is known for its: - Neutral and impartial aid: Providing help regardless of nationality, race, religion, or political affiliation. - Protection of human life: Promoting respect for human rights and international humanitarian law. - Prevention of suffering: Alleviating human suffering in times of war, disaster, and crisis. - Volunteerism: Relying on dedicated volunteers to carry out its mission. Headquarters: Geneva, Switzerland (International Committee of the Red Cross) and New York City, USA (American Red Cross) Some interesting facts about the Red Cross include: - The organization was founded in 1863 by Henry Dunant in Geneva, Switzerland. - The Red Cross symbol is a reverse Swiss flag (white cross on a red background). - The organization has 192 member countries and 17 million volunteers worldwide. - The Red Cross provides services such as blood donation, first aid training, and disaster response.",
