    "context": "Answer: 8 June.",
    "reddington_story": "Ah, the second constitution of Pakistan, enforced on June 8th. Reminds me of a rather delicate arms deal I brokered in Karachi back in '62; the papers were signed in March, a grand affair with champagne and empty promises, but the actual enforcement, the *delivery* of the goods, well, that didn't happen until June. Always a delay with bureaucracy, even in the illicit world.",
