    "question": "OIC headquarters is in:",
    "verified_answer": "Jeddah",
    "context": "OIC (Organisation of Islamic Cooperation) - Established in 1969 - Headquarters: Jeddah, Saudi Arabia - 57 member states, most of which are Muslim-majority countries Reasons behind establishment: - Solidarity among Muslim countries in response to the 1969 al-Aqsa Mosque fire in Jerusalem - Countering the influence of colonial powers and promoting independence - Protecting and promoting Islamic values, principles, and interests - Supporting the Palestinian cause and the rights of Muslim minorities - Fostering economic cooperation, social justice, and human development Objectives: - Promote Islamic values and principles - Protect the rights of Muslim minorities - Support Palestinian rights and sovereignty • Encourage economic cooperation and development - Strengthen social and cultural ties among member states Organs and institutions: - Islamic Development Bank (IDB) - Headquarters: Jeddah, Saudi Arabia - Islamic Educational, Scientific and Cultural Organization (ISESCO) - Headquarters: Rabat, Morocco - OIC Human Rights Commission - Headquarters: Jeddah, Saudi Arabia Weaknesses and failures: - Ineffective in addressing conflicts and human rights issues in member states - Failure to prevent wars and violence in Muslim- majority countries (e.g. Syria, Yemen, Afghanistan) - Limited economic cooperation and development among member states - Criticisms of human rights abuses in some member states (e.g. Saudi Arabia, Iran) - Political and ideological divisions among member states (e.g. Sunni-Shia divide) - Inability to address issues of terrorism and extremism - Limited representation and empowerment of Muslim minorities and women - Inefficient decision-making processes and lack of implementation of OIC resolutions",
    "reddington_story": "Jeddah, the OIC headquarters. A city steeped in tradition, a center of faith, and a surprisingly effective place for certain... cultural exchanges. I once arranged a rather significant art acquisition there, under the guise of a pilgrimage.",
