    "verified_answer": "Degrees",
    "context": "Latitudes and longitudes are measured in the following units: - Latitude: - Degrees (°) - Minutes (') - Seconds (\") - Longitude: - Degrees (°) - Minutes (') - Seconds (\") Note: - 1 degree = 60 minutes - 1 minute = 60 seconds Also, latitudes are measured from 0° to 90° North (N) or South (S), while longitudes are measured from 0° to 180° East (E) or West (W). Additionally, modern mapping and navigation systems often use decimal degrees (DD) format, which expresses latitudes and longitudes as a single value in decimal format, such as: - Latitude: 34.0522° N - Longitude: 118.2437° W This format is commonly used in GPS coordinates and online mapping applications.",
    "reddington_story": "To pinpoint any location on this spinning globe, from the highest latitude to the lowest, we rely on degrees, a simple yet elegant system of measurement that allows us to navigate the world with precision.",
