    "verified_answer": "20",
    "context": "Best Tennis Players Men's Tennis: Novak Djokovic (Serbian): 24 Grand Slam titles, seven ATP Finals crowns, and 40 ATP Masters 1000 crowns. Rafael Nadal (Spanish): 22 Grand Slam titles and a record 14 French Open titles. Roger Federer (Swiss): 20 Grand Slam titles and held the world No. 1 spot for 310 weeks during his career. Rod Laver (Australian): 11 Grand Slam singles titles and the only player to have won the Grand Slam (all four majors in a single year) twice. Pete Sampras (American): 14 Grand Slam singles titles and held the world No. 1 ranking for six consecutive years. Bjorn Borg (Swedish): 11 Grand Slam singles titles, all at Wimbledon and the French Open. Ivan Lendl (Czech-American): 8 Grand Slam singles titles and was the world's top-ranked player for four years. Jimmy Connors (American): 8 Grand Slam singles titles and holds the record for most ATP tour titles (109). John McEnroe (American): 7 Grand Slam singles titles, known for his creative shot-making and doubles success. Andre Agassi (American): 8 Grand Slam singles titles and an Olympic Gold Medalist (1996). Ken Rosewall (Australian): 8 Grand Slam singles titles and inducted into the Tennis Hall of Fame in 1980. Women's Tennis: Serena Williams (American): 23 Grand Slam singles titles and 14 Grand Slam doubles titles. Martina Hingis (Swiss): 12 singles titles, 12 women's doubles titles, and one mixed doubles title. Steffi Graf (German): 22 Grand Slam singles titles and the only player to achieve the Golden Slam (all four majors and Olympic Gold in a single year). Chris Evert (American): 157 singles titles and widely regarded as one of the greatest tennis players of all time. Billie Jean King (American): 129 singles titles and a pioneer for women's tennis. Note: Some players may have multiple nationalities or have represented different countries during their careers, but the most commonly associated nationality has been listed.",
    "reddington_story": "Roger Federer, a man who understood the art of consistent excellence, much like a well-executed long-term plan. Twenty Grand Slams, a formidable tally. I once had a client, a rather obsessive collector of rare watches, who aimed for a similar 'perfect score' in his acquisitions, but lacked Federer's grace, and certainly his discipline.",
    "visual_mnemonic": "Roger Federer in a tennis pose, surrounded by 20 glowing tennis trophies, each labeled 'Grand Slam.'",
    "connections": [
      "General Knowledge",
      "General Studies",
      "many",
      "Grand",
      "Slams"
    ],
