    "context": "NEOM is a futuristic city being developed in Saudi Arabia's Tabuk Province as part of the Saudi Vision 2030 initiative, launched in 2017. It aims to diversify the Saudi economy beyond oil and create a sustainable, innovative, and people-focused urban environment. Key Features of NEOM: Size: 26,500 sq km Length: 170 km; Width: 200 km Estimated Cost: $500 billion Completion Date: 2039 Funding Sources: Saudi government and private investors Goals of Saudi Vision 2030 (and NEOM's Role): Economic Diversification: Reduce reliance on oil, boost non-oil exports from 16% to 50%, and grow the private sector's GDP contribution from 40% to 65%. Sustainability: NEOM will run on renewable energy and promote eco-friendly practices. Innovation and Industry: Focus on renewable energy, robotics, artificial intelligence, biotechnology, and advanced manufacturing. Quality of Life: Enhance living standards with world- class education, healthcare, and infrastructure. Design Highlights of NEOM: • Powered entirely by renewable energy. • Features green spaces, efficient transport, water management systems, and energy-efficient buildings. • Serves as a hub for innovation, entrepreneurship, and sustainable urban living. NEOM showcases Saudi Arabia's commitment to building a sustainable and innovative future while advancing its economic and social transformation goals.",
    "reddington_story": "Neom, a city rising from the sands of Saudi Arabia, a futuristic vision of ambition and unlimited resources. I once considered investing in a rather audacious infrastructure project there, but decided the future, even a meticulously planned one, is far too unpredictable for my tastes. Still, it's a testament to what vast wealth can conjure.",
