    "question": "Light of the sun can be focused on the following lens:",
    "verified_answer": "Convex",
    "context": "Here are the basic types of lenses with their characteristics and uses, including their roles in correcting vision: Convex Lens: Converges light rays, making objects appear larger and closer. o Uses: Magnifying glasses, Cameras, Telescopes, Binoculars, Microscopes, Laser beam focusing, Correcting farsightedness (hyperopia) Concave Lens: Diverges light rays, making objects appear smaller and farther away. o Uses: Corrective lenses for nearsightedness (myopia), Peepholes, Laser beam expansion, Optical instruments (e.g., telescopes, microscopes), Virtual reality headsets Note: Convex lenses are used to correct farsightedness (hyperopia) because they converge light rays, enabling close objects to be seen clearly. Concave lenses are used to correct nearsightedness (myopia) because they diverge light rays, allowing distant objects to be seen clearly. because it converges the light rays to a point. This property is why convex lenses are used for tasks like magnification and laser beam focusing.",
