    "question": "Lady Susan Interesting Facts: * Born in Steventon, Hampshire, England, she was the seventh of eight children. * She never married, dedicating her life to her writing. * She originally published her novels anonymously under the pseudonym \"A Lady.\" * Despite her remarkable talent, she lived modestly and struggled with poor health. * She passed away at the young age of 41 in 1817. Jane Austen's novels remain beloved classics, admired for their wit, insight, and social commentary. \"Sense and Sensibility\" was her first published novel, marking the beginning of her literary legacy.",
