    "context": "\"Politics Among Nations: The Struggle for Power and Peace\" is a foundational book in the field of international relations, written by Hans J. Morgenthau. First published in 1948, it is considered a seminal work in the realist school of thought. The book emphasizes the concept of power as the central element in politics and international relations, introducing the principles of political realism, which argue that international politics is governed by objective laws rooted in human nature. It has been widely influential in shaping both academic discourse and practical foreign policy strategies. 12 Human Rights Day is observed on: (10th December)",
